		<title>06STUBBLE BURNING ON THE DOWNS</title>
		<content> This is a long established practice   
 and used by all the local farmers to  
 get rid of the stubble and harmful    
 insect pests.  As the soil is light   
 and full of flints a short stalked    
 grain has been bred to stand up to the
 strong winds and driving rain.  On    
 very fertile soils farmers get about 3
 tons to the acre of cereal crops,     
 using fertilisers and chemical sprays,
 depending on the weather, but most    
 average about 2\ tons to the acre.    
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
